50|$|The <b>pygmy</b> <b>falcon,</b> or African <b>pygmy</b> <b>falcon</b> (Polihierax semitorquatus), is a falcon {{that lives}} in eastern and {{southern}} Africa and is the smallest raptor on the continent. As a small falcon, only 19 to 20 cm long, it preys on insects, small reptiles, and small mammals.|$|E
