50|$|Research in {{molecular}} genetics has {{also found that}} the white-rumped falcon is more closely related to the Falco falcons than it is to the <b>pygmy</b> <b>falcon,</b> and indicates two major clades within the extant members of the falcon subfamily, Falconinae. Boyd places the Microhierax falconets with the <b>pygmy</b> <b>falcon</b> in tribe Polihieracini, and the white-rumped falcon as Neohierax insignis in tribe Falconini.|$|E
